1. The CFFFQ estimated total daily calcium intake.
2. The 24-hour recall estimated total daily calcium intake.
3. The CFFFQ estimated a greater total daily calcium intake than the 24-hour recall.
4. The mean total daily calcium intake estimated by the CFFFQ was 1,021 mg/d.
5. The standard deviation of the total daily calcium intake estimated by the CFFFQ was 624 mg/d.
6. The mean total daily calcium intake estimated by the 24-hour recall was 800 mg/d.
7. The standard deviation of the total daily calcium intake estimated by the 24-hour recall was 433 mg/d.
8. The difference in the total daily calcium intake estimated by the CFFFQ and the 24-hour recall was statistically significant (P < .001).
